news.title: Anant Raj's net profit increases by 75% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Anant Raj's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 523.75 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 53.67 per cent from Rs 340.83 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Greenply Industries' net profit rises 26.33% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Greenply Industries' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 642.45 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 12.52 per cent from Rs 570.97 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: NBCC to re-develop projects worth Rs 10,000 crore in Goa
news.para: In the first phase, NBCC will execute six projects with an estimated value of more than Rs 1,700 crore. The total plot area of these projects is around 53,000 sq meter, with a built-up area of approximately 1,85,000 sq meter.

news.title: LIC Housing Finance's net profit up 11.20% in Q2 FY25
news.para: LIC Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 6,938.31 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 2.55 per cent from Rs 6,765.87 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: SRG Housing Finance's net profit up 25.48% in Q2 FY25
news.para: SRG Housing Finance's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 36.84 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 18.11 per cent from Rs 31.19 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Ajmera Realty's net profit grows 58.26% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Ajmera Realty's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 204.12 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 38.30 per cent from Rs 147.59 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Nilkamal's net profit increases by 30.27% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Nilkamal's net consolidated total income stood at Rs 824.37 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 5.44 per cent from Rs 781.85 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body to relocate Narmada trunk line under commercial plot on sale
news.para: Since no construction can take place on the plot in TP Scheme No. 76/B even if sold, the civic body has decided to move the line at a cost of Rs 5.29 crore. A proposal for the project was approved at the meeting of AMC's water and sewage committee held on Monday.

news.title: Ambuja Cements' net profit dips 52.10% in Q2 FY25
news.para: Ambuja Cements' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 7,890.14 crore in Q2 FY25 as against Rs 7,899.99 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: RIICO drafts rules for direct land allotment in Rajasthan
news.para: The current practice of land auctions, which increases prices, has been widely criticised and is often cited as the major roadblock behind Rajasthan's slow progress in industrial development in the past.

news.title: Residents protest in Sancoale against proposed Bhutani Infra development project
news.para: Gathering under the banner of Sancoale Against Mega Project (SAMP), the protesters demanded that state govt revoke any construction licence issued to the multi-dwelling housing project with immediate effect.

news.title: MCD proposes Rs 1,144 crore plan to replace four lakh LED lights across four zones
news.para: The proposal, costing Rs 1,144.3 crore, also includes the operation and maintenance of lights for 10 years. It will be presented in the House meeting on Monday for administrative approval and expenditure sanction.

news.title: Bengaluru civic body to survey under-construction buildings
news.para: The move follows the collapse of an under-construction building at Babusapalya near Hennur last week in which nine people were killed.

news.title: Max Estates posts net loss of Rs 1.38 crore in Q2 FY25
news.para: Max Estates' net consolidated total income stood at Rs 52.77 crore in Q2 FY25, a growth of 89.96 per cent from Rs 27.78 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Kerala: Vilappilsala mini-township project likely to be scrapped
news.para: The works related to the Rs 400 crore project, planned at the old waste treatment plant, came to a standstill earlier this year. Although earlier, the corporation officials expressed hope that the project could be revived, the chances are slim.

news.title: NCLT dismisses JC Flowers’ Rs 70 crore claim against HDIL
news.para: NCLT said, "ruling that the debt did not qualify as a “financial debt” under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code (IBC) as it was not due or payable at the time of HDIL’s corporate insolvency resolution process (CIRP) commencement."

news.title: Over 8,000 flats registered in Greater Noida under rehabilitation policy
news.para: Another 8,000 flats are likely to be registered by March next year, according to a report presented to the Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority's (GNIDA) board on Sunday.

news.title: Haryana RERA recovers only Rs 225 crore out of Rs 1,043 crore owed to homebuyers
news.para: H-Rera was set up following the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act of 2016 to protect the interests of homebuyers and ensure accountability in the real estate sector.

news.title: Noida authority approves two more projects under co-development policy
news.para: Noida authority has approved two projects under Uttar Pradesh’s co-development policy, allowing Nimbus Projects and Theme County to revive stalled projects in sectors 168 and 115, respectively. The initiative aims to aid 1,000 homebuyers and ensures payment of dues and financial closure by the new developers.

news.title: Jaipur development body set to expand by 1,000 sq km, with 272 more villages
news.para: "A meeting chaired by JDA commissioner Anandhi will be held in early Nov to finalise the proposed area extensions under the JDA's jurisdiction in the Master Plan 2047," a JDA official said.
